Who Am I ?

About Me

I'm a UX/UI designer with a passion for crafting intuitive and user-centered experiences. But my journey doesn't begin with pixels and prototypes. I'm deeply driven by in-depth user research, particularly ethnographic methods. By stepping into users' worlds, observing their behaviors, and understanding their needs in context, I can design interfaces that truly resonate. This research focus allows me to bridge the gap between creativity and empathy, ensuring my designs are not just beautiful, but fundamentally solve user problems.

What I Do ?

Bring ideas to life through quick visualization and iteration.
